{
  "texts": [
    "Conversational models including LLM chatbots are expected to be broadly used for various nutrition-related tasks, such as diet recommendations and recipes generation 1, 3.",
    "Our findings offer insights into the readiness, potential, and limitations of these models, since the RD exam consists of a wide range of topics designed to assess a dietitian's competency.",
    "The performance of the chatbots on the RD exam can reflect their ability to comprehend nutrition queries, understand fundamentals of dietetics, and transform the knowledge into nutrition management, care, and reliable advice.",
    "These findings show the potential of LLM chatbots to be effectively used to support decision-making in practice and enhance dietitian support applications, including patient assessment, nutrition plan generation, and providing accurate answers to nutrition inquiries.",
    "Additionally, our results highlight the role of prompt engineering on improving the accuracy and consistency of the models."
  ]
}